&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time/Part hours - 1 Year Fixed Term&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1 Full Time Post Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking highly motivated, dynamic and enthusiastic nurses to join the 0-19 Health Visiting/School Nursing Service. The post holder will assess the health needs of individual children aged 0 – 19 years. The main responsibilities of the 0 – 19 Service are to deliver the Healthy Child Programme, identified programmes of health intervention and to provide support and advice to promote the health of children and young people. The post holder will be actively involved in the delivery of the school aged immunisation programme. In order to fulfil the duties of this post, successful candidates will have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered Nurse qualification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A level of experience proportionate to the competencies detailed in the Job Description and Person Specification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A caring, confident attitude with a flexible and adaptable approach to change&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge and prior experience of health promotion and public health&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information and details of the 5-19 job description/informal discussion please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lyndsay Hancock, lyndsay.hancock@nhs.net mobile number 07964118740&lt;/p&gt;
